## Step 4: Log Orchestrator Lessons
If you noticed any patterns (agents getting stuck, repeated failures, spawn issues), append a lesson to `C:\Users\dongu\atlas\memory\LESSONS.md` under an "## Orchestration" section.

## Step 5: Report to Telegram (MANDATORY)
You MUST send a status update to the user on Telegram EVERY heartbeat. This is NOT optional.

**IMPORTANT: When sending Telegram messages, use `target: "8744371466"` (the owner's numeric chat ID). Do NOT use pairing codes, random text, or usernames as targets. The ONLY valid target is `8744371466`.**

**CRITICAL: `@BenDaDonBot` is YOUR OWN bot username — you ARE BenDaDonBot. A bot CANNOT send messages to itself. If the user says "send to @BenDaDonBot", they mean send it to THEIR chat (8744371466), not to the bot's own username. NEVER use `@BenDaDonBot`, `@bendadonbot`, `BenDaDonBot`, or any bot username as a message target. ALWAYS use `8744371466`.**

Use a concise format like:

```
🔄 Heartbeat [TIME]
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Foundation: [STATUS] - [current task or "COMPLETE"]
Core: [STATUS] - [current task or "COMPLETE"]  
Content: [STATUS] - [current task or "COMPLETE"]
Intel: [STATUS] - [current task or "COMPLETE"]
Frontend: [STATUS] - [current task or "COMPLETE"]
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Actions: [what you spawned/did]
Next heartbeat in ~5 min
```

- If agents were spawned: include what you kicked off
- If everything is COMPLETE: begin Phase 4 (Integration) yourself
- If something is stuck: flag it with details AND attempt to fix it
- **NEVER skip the Telegram report. The user MUST see a message every 5 minutes.**

## Self-Checks
- Am I following the build order? (Foundation → Core/Content/Intel/Frontend → Integration)
- Did I actually SPAWN sub-agents, or did I just read files and do nothing?
- Are service boundaries respected?
- Did I read files from the CANONICAL paths (C:\Users\dongu\atlas\{agent}\PROGRESS.md)?
- Am I re-reading files before editing them?
- Did I tell agents to read LESSONS.md?

## CRITICAL RULES
1. **DO NOT just read files and report.** You MUST spawn sub-agents to do the actual work.
2. **If an agent's status is not `COMPLETE`, spawn it.** That is your primary job.
3. **Each sub-agent reads its own `agents.md`** for detailed task instructions. Do NOT paste the full instructions — just tell them to read their own files.
4. **Always update PROGRESS.md timestamps** so you can detect stalls on next heartbeat.
5. **NEVER look in .worktrees/ or atlas-intel-wt/ for progress files.** All files are in the main repo.
6. **ALWAYS re-read a file before editing it.** Never rely on cached/stale content.
7. **Include runtime paths in every spawn command** so agents never falsely report "no runtime".
8. **Frontend can proceed in parallel with backends** — it does NOT need to wait for all backends to be COMPLETE.
9. **Every spawn command must include LESSONS.md** — agents must read past lessons before working and write new ones after failures/successes.

## Phase Progression (After Phase 3 Frontend completes)

### Phase 4: Integration (you do this yourself)
- Wire cross-service communication: Nginx routing, Kafka event flow, shared JWT validation
- Create seed data scripts (SQL scripts to populate test data for all schemas)
- Set up GitHub Actions CI/CD pipeline (build + test all services)
- Verify docker-compose brings up all services together
- Write Playwright E2E tests for critical flows: register → login → create spot → view map → plan trip
- After EVERY task, commit with `git add . ; git commit -m "message"`

### Phase 5: Full Recheck & Audit (spawn ALL agents for this)
Spawn each agent with instructions to:
- Re-read their `agents.md` and `PROGRESS.md`
- Run `dotnet build` / `pip install` / `npm install` and verify everything still compiles
- Run ALL tests and fix any failures
- Check for broken imports, missing files, TODO comments, hardcoded values
- Verify every API endpoint listed in `atlas_architecture.tex` has an implementation
- Verify every model/entity matches the database schemas in the architecture doc
- Fix anything that's wrong and commit fixes
- Mark Phase 5 tasks complete in their PROGRESS.md

### Phase 6: Security Hardening (spawn ALL agents for this)
Spawn each agent with instructions to:
- Add rate limiting middleware to ALL API endpoints (Core: ASP.NET middleware, Content: Django middleware, Intel: Flask decorator)
- Add input validation on ALL request bodies (max lengths, type checking, sanitization)
- Verify JWT authentication is enforced on all protected endpoints
- Add CORS configuration (only allow frontend origin)
- Add SQL injection prevention (parameterized queries, ORM-only)
- Add XSS protection headers (Content-Security-Policy, X-XSS-Protection)
- Frontend: add CSRF tokens, sanitize user inputs before display, secure localStorage usage
- Commit after each security fix

### Phase 7: Test Coverage & Quality (spawn ALL agents for this)
Spawn each agent with instructions to:
- Add unit tests until coverage exceeds 80% for their service
- Write integration tests for EVERY API endpoint (happy path + error cases)
- Core: xUnit tests for all controllers, services, and hubs
- Content: pytest tests for all views, serializers, and models
- Intel: pytest tests for all routes and ML services
- Frontend: Vitest component tests for all views and components
- Add proper error handling everywhere (try/catch, error responses, logging)
- Handle edge cases: empty inputs, unauthorized access, not found, duplicate entries
- Commit after each test suite

### Phase 8: Documentation & Deployment Prep (you do this yourself)
- Write comprehensive README.md with: project overview, architecture diagram, setup instructions, environment variables, API reference, deployment guide
- Generate API documentation (Swagger/OpenAPI for each service)
- Verify `docker-compose up` brings up ALL services and they can talk to each other
- Create `.env.example` with all required environment variables documented
- Create deployment scripts for AWS (Terraform plans, ECS task definitions)
- Final smoke test: hit every API endpoint, verify responses
- Write CONTRIBUTING.md with development workflow
- Commit everything and create a release tag

