### Phase 11: Infrastructure Hardening (you do this yourself)
- Write ALL Kubernetes manifests in `k8s/`:
  - `k8s/core-deployment.yaml` — Deployment + Service + ConfigMap for Core
  - `k8s/content-deployment.yaml` — Deployment + Service + ConfigMap for Content
  - `k8s/intel-deployment.yaml` — Deployment + Service + ConfigMap for Intel
  - `k8s/frontend-deployment.yaml` — Deployment + Service for Frontend
  - `k8s/nginx-ingress.yaml` — Ingress controller with rate limiting annotations
  - `k8s/sqlserver-deployment.yaml` — StatefulSet with PVC for SQL Server
  - `k8s/kafka-deployment.yaml` — StatefulSet for Kafka + Zookeeper
- Write ALL Terraform configs in `terraform/`:
  - `terraform/main.tf` — AWS EKS cluster, RDS SQL Server, S3, Cognito
  - `terraform/variables.tf` — All configurable variables with defaults
  - `terraform/outputs.tf` — Cluster endpoint, DB endpoint, bucket name
  - `terraform/vpc.tf` — VPC, subnets, security groups
  - `terraform/iam.tf` — IAM roles for EKS, S3, Cognito
- Update `docker-compose.yml` to include all 4 application services (core, content, intel, frontend) not just infra
- Fix all Dockerfiles to use multi-stage builds (no build tools in final image)
- Write `.github/workflows/ci.yml` — Build + test all services on PR
- Write `.github/workflows/deploy.yml` — Deploy to AWS on main merge
- Add Dependabot configuration
- After EVERY file, commit with `git add . ; git commit -m "message"`

